#: ../../../autoapi/tilelang/layout/layout/index.rst:82
msgid ""
"This is useful for building a larger layout by tiling an \"atom\" layout. "
"Conceptually, repeating on dimension ``dim`` with ``factor`` constructs a "
"new layout ``L'`` such that::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../autoapi/tilelang/layout/layout/index.rst:86
msgid "L'(*idx) = [idx[dim] // extent_dim] + L(idx with idx[dim] % extent_dim)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../autoapi/tilelang/layout/layout/index.rst:88
msgid "where ``extent_dim`` is the original extent of the repeated dimension."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../autoapi/tilelang/layout/layout/index.rst:90
msgid "The input dimension to repeat (0-based, supports negative indexing)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../autoapi/tilelang/layout/layout/index.rst:92
msgid "The repeat factor. Must be a positive integer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../autoapi/tilelang/layout/layout/index.rst:95
msgid ""
"A new Layout with the repeated input shape and an extra leading output "
"dimension representing the repeat-group index."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../autoapi/tilelang/layout/layout/index.rst:103
msgid "Expand (lift) this layout by prepending new leading input dimensions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../autoapi/tilelang/layout/layout/index.rst:105
msgid ""
"The new leading dimensions are forwarded unchanged to the output, and the "
"original layout is applied to the remaining trailing dimensions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../autoapi/tilelang/layout/layout/index.rst:109
msgid "Example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../autoapi/tilelang/layout/layout/index.rst:110
msgid ""
"Given a 2D layout ``L`` over ``[J, K]``, you can lift it to a 3D layout over "
"``[I, J, K]`` by::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../autoapi/tilelang/layout/layout/index.rst:113
msgid ""
"L3 = L.expand([I])\n"
"# [i, j, k] -> [i, *L(j, k)]"
msgstr ""

